        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 3:48PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 348 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southeast of Harlowton, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail, along with
brief heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deadmans Basin Reservoir and Shawmut.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
